---
name: map-ops
also-codegen: v2
---

# `Map` access on every backend

Pins the `Map` access surface across all codegen lanes. Until 2026-07-19 the
**v2-JS** backend (`run-js --v2`) crashed on `Map` access: `m("a")` threw
`not callable: <map>` (a map value applied as a function) and `.get`/`.size`
had no dispatch — while native and JVM-bytecode had full parity
(`specs/v2-state-2026-07-18.md` §R2). This case exercises `apply`/`get`/
`getOrElse`/`size`/`contains`/`isEmpty` so a v2-JS regression fails the suite
(`v2-f6-backends` J2).

Only scalar-returning ops are pinned here: `keys`/`values`/`toList` and whole-map
printing render differently across v1 vs v2 (v1 maps are unordered and v1-JVM
renders keys as `Set`/values as `Iterable`), so they cannot share one expected
file — the v2-JS parity on those is covered by the differential dev harness.

```scalascript
val m = Map("a" -> 1, "b" -> 2, "c" -> 3)
println(m("a"))
println(m("c"))
println(m.get("b"))
println(m.get("z"))
println(m.getOrElse("c", 0))
println(m.getOrElse("z", 99))
println(m.size)
println(m.isEmpty)
println(m.nonEmpty)
println(m.contains("a"))
println(m.contains("z"))
val n = Map(1 -> "x", 2 -> "y")
println(n(1))
println(n.get(2))
println(n.get(3))
println(n.size)
println(n.contains(1))
```
